cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with statistical machine translation (SMT) which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as SMT involves the use of machine learning algorithms and AI techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of decoder implementation for modern multicore servers, which could fall under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
